SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:museum,science,family,educators
DESCRIPTION:Organizer: Field Museum - Events\\nCost: Ticket required\\nAge
 s: All ages\\nCategory: General\\n\\nJoin us for a professional developmen
 t workshop inspired by the Restoring Earth in Abbott Hall. This session wi
 ll explore how rainforest ecosystems can be used to support inquiry-based 
 science learning in grades 3–5. The workshop will highlight classroom st
 rategies that support Next Generation Science Standards (NGSS)\, with a fo
 cus on ecosystem relationships\, environmental change\, and human impacts 
 on Earth’s systems. Educators will explore approaches for modeling food 
 webs\, facilitating evidence-based discussions\, and helping students anal
 yze real-world environmental challenges. As a special incentive\, the firs
 t 10 educators to register will receive a complimentary copy of Three Week
 s in the Rainforest by Jennifer Swanson\, a STEM book inspired by the rese
 arch and themes featured in the exhibition.\\n\\nMore info: https://www.fi
 eldmuseum.org/our-events/professional-development-for-educators/restoring-
 earth-investigating-ecosystems-and-human-impact-in-the-amazon-rainfores
LOCATION:Field Museum\, 1400 S Lake Shore Dr\, Chicago\, IL 60605
URL:https://www.fieldmuseum.org/our-events/professional-development-for-ed
 ucators/restoring-earth-investigating-ecosystems-and-human-impact-in-the-a
 mazon-rainfores
